value.value: A white patch or plaque on the oral cavity mucosa that cannot be characterized clinically or pathologically as any other disease. The diagnosis of leukoplakia is one of exclusion; other conditions such as candidiasis, lichen planus, leukoedema, etc., must be ruled out before a diagnosis of leukoplakia can be made. Leukoplakia may be a premalignant condition.
A malignant tumor that has spread from its original (primary) site of growth to another site close to or distant from the primary site.
A very rare benign neoplasm that metastasizes inexplicably. This category includes metastasizing pleomorphic adenoma of the salivary gland and uterine corpus metastasizing leiomyoma.

The most common variant of adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma.  It is characterized by systemic disease with a leukemic phase, generalized lymphadenopathy, and skin lesions.  Hypercalcemia is commonly seen.

An adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma characterized by generalized lymphadenopathy without peripheral blood involvement.  Most patients have advanced disease, however hypercalcemia is not frequently present.
A rare morphologic variant of adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma characterized by the presence of Hodgkin-like and Reed-Sternberg-like cells.

A neoplasm that arises from the spinal cord and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: T-Cell Prolymphocytic Leukemia, Small Cell Variant

value.value: A T-cell prolymphocytic leukemia characterized by the presence of small neoplastic prolymphocytes often with invisible nucleolus by light microscopy.

label.value: T-Cell Prolymphocytic Leukemia, Cerebriform Cell Variant

value.value: A T-cell prolymphocytic leukemia characterized by the presence of neoplastic prolymphocytes with irregular or cerebriform nuclear outline.

label.value: Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia with Plasmacytoid Differentiation

value.value: A chronic lymphocytic leukemia characterized by the presence of neoplastic lymphocytes with plasmacytoid morphology.

label.value: Small Lymphocytic Lymphoma with Plasmacytoid Differentiation

value.value: A small lymphocytic lymphoma characterized by the presence of neoplastic lymphocytes with plasmacytoid morphology.

label.value: Splenic Marginal Zone Lymphoma without Villous Lymphocytes

value.value: A term that refers to the classification of a clinical or laboratory finding according to the anatomic site or system that is involved.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the digestive system.

A neoplasm that arises from the thyroid gland and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the nervous system.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the integumentary system.

Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the urinary system.
An anatomic abnormality that is either present at birth or appears later in life.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the connective and soft tissue.
Symptoms, physical examination results, and/or laboratory test results related to the hematopoietic system.

A neoplasm that arises from the adrenal gland and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.
Contact with a chemical substance through touch, inhalation, or ingestion.
The outcome of a laboratory test.
A peripheral blood finding in which a large number of erythrocytes are shaped in a slightly oval-shaped form.
An additional finding not previously noted.
A finding indicating that a malignant neoplasm has spread to regional lymph nodes.

A semisynthetic, broad-spectrum antibiotic derived from Streptomyces venequelae with primarily bacteriostatic activity. Chloramphenicol diffuses through the bacterial cell wall and reversibly binds to the bacterial 50S ribosomal subunit. The binding interferes with peptidyl transferase activity, thereby prevents transfer of amino acids to the growing peptide chains and blocks peptide bond formation. As a result bacterial protein synthesis is blocked and impede bacterial cell proliferation.

A neoplasm that arises from the parathyroid glands and is characterized by the absence of atypical or malignant cytological and architectural features, and absence of invasive features or metastatic potential.

label.value: Metastatic Breast Carcinoma in the Lung

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the breast and has metastasized to the lung.

label.value: Metastatic Breast Carcinoma in the Brain

value.value: A carcinoma that has spread to the brain from its original site in the breast, through the hematogenous route.

label.value: Metastatic Breast Carcinoma in the Liver

value.value: A carcinoma that originates from the breast and has spread to the liver.

label.value: Metastatic Breast Carcinoma in the Bone

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the breast and has metastasized to the bone.

label.value: Metastatic Lung Carcinoma in the Brain

value.value: A carcinoma that has spread to the brain from its original site in the lung, through the hematogenous route.

label.value: Metastatic Lung Carcinoma in the Bone

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the lung and has metastasized to the bone.

label.value: Metastatic Lung Carcinoma in the Liver

value.value: A carcinoma that originates from the lung and has spread to the liver.

label.value: Prostate Carcinoma Metastatic in the Lung

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the prostate gland and has spread to the lungs.

label.value: Prostate Carcinoma Metastatic in the Bone

label.value: Colon Carcinoma Metastatic in the Liver
